first_reading.text:
[[Jr 1,17]]The word of the LORD came to Jeremiah: “Gird your loins; stand up and tell them all that I command you. Do not be terrified on account of them, or I will terrify you before them;
[[Jr 1,18]]For I am the one who today makes you a fortified city, a pillar of iron, a wall of bronze, against the whole land: against Judah’s kings and princes, its priests and the people of the land.
[[Jr 1,19]]They will fight against you, but not prevail over you, for I am with you to deliver you, says the LORD.
